

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="archetypes"
  description="archetypes index / hero, shadow, anima, animus, child, trickster, wise old man"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">archetypes / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>archetypes</h1>
    <p>
      recurring patterns of human experience that appear across myth, dream,
      story, and inner life. not fixed identities, but living structures.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      these forms shape perception, behavior, and meaning beneath the surface of
      personality.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/archetypes/hero">
          <span class="link-title">hero</span>
          <span class="link-desc">effort, will, journey, overcoming, identity.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype">
          <span class="link-title">shadow</span>
          <span class="link-desc">repressed self, denied traits, hidden forces.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/anima">
          <span class="link-title">anima</span>
          <span class="link-desc">inner feminine, feeling, image, soul-depth.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/animus">
          <span class="link-title">animus</span>
          <span class="link-desc">inner masculine, structure, word, direction.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/child">
          <span class="link-title">child</span>
          <span class="link-desc">innocence, potential, vulnerability, beginning.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/trickster">
          <span class="link-title">trickster</span>
          <span class="link-desc">disruption, paradox, inversion, breaking form.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/archetypes/wise-old-man">
          <span class="link-title">wise old man</span>
          <span class="link-desc">guidance, insight, pattern, deep knowing.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        archetypes are not roles you choose. they are patterns that move through
        you. at different points in life, different archetypes become active.
      </p>
      <p>
        the goal is not to become one archetype, but to become aware of their
        movement and relationship within you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">archetypes map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/archetypes/hero" class="link-blue">hero</a> — effort, struggle, identity</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype" class="link-red">shadow</a> — repression, hidden self</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/anima" class="link-green">anima</a> — inner image, feeling</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/animus">animus</a> — structure, direction, logos</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/child">child</a> — potential, vulnerability</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/trickster">trickster</a> — disruption, inversion</p>
      <p><a href="/archetypes/wise-old-man">wise old man</a> — wisdom, guidance</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this section follows a sequence, but each archetype can be entered from any point.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>